From 7a04e3aaaa9d058f416531819efdd0bbf2c37870 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sean Smith <DefendTheDisabled@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Apr 2026 15:57:34 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 02/16] vfs: extend struct file_attr with ptime (VER1, 40
 bytes)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Extends struct file_attr from VER0 (24 bytes) to VER1 (40 bytes)
by adding ptime_sec (__s64), ptime_nsec (__u32), and ptime_pad
(__u32 for alignment) at offsets 24, 32, 36 respectively. The
timestamp encoding matches statx: __s64 seconds + __u32
nanoseconds, giving ~292 billion years range and nanosecond
precision.

file_attr uses size-versioning via copy_struct_from/to_user()
(same pattern as clone_args, mount_attr, statx). Userspace passes
the struct size it knows about; the kernel zero-fills unknown
trailing fields for forward compatibility. ptime is the first
timestamp field in file_attr — prior VER0 carried only xflags,
extsize, nextents, projid, cowextsize.

Padding is required because VER1 must be a multiple of 8 bytes
for alignment. ptime_pad is reserved and must be zero on write.

This layout was confirmed with Wong (XFS maintainer) during the
v2 migration discussion. The dual-dispatch approach in
file_setattr keeps ptime (iattr path) separate from xflags
(vfs_fileattr_set path) because ntfs3, FAT, and exFAT do not
implement .fileattr_set but all implement .setattr.

Ref: Decision #71 (file_attr migration per Wong's suggestion)
Ref: Decision #72 (iattr dispatch path, not .fileattr_set)
Ref: Wong email thread on lore.kernel.org (2026-04-07)
---
 include/uapi/linux/fs.h | 7 ++++++-
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/include/uapi/linux/fs.h b/include/uapi/linux/fs.h
index 66ca526cf786..d6d9cd542aea 100644
--- a/include/uapi/linux/fs.h
+++ b/include/uapi/linux/fs.h
@@ -229,10 +229,15 @@ struct file_attr {
 	__u32 fa_nextents;	/* nextents field value (get)   */
 	__u32 fa_projid;	/* project identifier (get/set) */
 	__u32 fa_cowextsize;	/* CoW extsize field value (get/set) */
+	/* ptime (provenance time) extension — VER1 */
+	__s64 fa_ptime_sec;	/* provenance time: seconds since epoch */
+	__u32 fa_ptime_nsec;	/* provenance time: nanoseconds */
+	__u32 fa_ptime_pad;	/* alignment padding */
 };
 
 #define FILE_ATTR_SIZE_VER0 24
-#define FILE_ATTR_SIZE_LATEST FILE_ATTR_SIZE_VER0
+#define FILE_ATTR_SIZE_VER1 (FILE_ATTR_SIZE_VER0 + 16)
+#define FILE_ATTR_SIZE_LATEST FILE_ATTR_SIZE_VER1
 
 /*
  * Flags for the fsx_xflags field
